WEBVTT

00:06.341 --> 00:08.134
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

01:24.335 --> 01:27.172
I need some kind of sign from you.
I need an indication,

01:27.297 --> 01:29.466
- some kind of indication, that you...
- What?

01:29.674 --> 01:31.926
...fully understand the stupidity of this.

01:32.010 --> 01:34.387
REBECCA: I do.
DON: Doesn't feel like it.

01:34.471 --> 01:36.431
How would you like me to behave?

01:36.514 --> 01:40.059
It feels to me... I have to say,
it feels to me like you think this is nuance,

01:40.143 --> 01:42.061
that you think there are layers
that have to be explored.

01:42.145 --> 01:43.104
Why do you say that?

01:43.188 --> 01:45.523
DON: Well, for one thing,
there's four lawyers in the room

01:45.607 --> 01:48.735
billing out at, I don't know.
I'm sure you're worth it.

01:48.818 --> 01:51.196
And you've been here five days.
This is your fifth day.

01:51.362 --> 01:53.823
But that's my point.
Why do we need lawyers who are worth it?

01:53.907 --> 01:56.659
Why do we need lawyers?
Why do we need lawyers?

01:56.743 --> 01:59.204
- You're being sued.
- And you're saying that like it's not insane.

01:59.287 --> 02:01.372
You're saying that like it isn't...

02:05.710 --> 02:06.836
Tell me what I'm missing.

02:07.295 --> 02:08.797
A producer comes up from DC.

02:08.880 --> 02:10.965
He wants to make a name
for himself in New York.

02:11.049 --> 02:14.803
He chases a story that's not there.
And the story, it's not a kitten up a tree.

02:14.886 --> 02:17.972
Chemical weapons, sarin gas on civilians.

02:18.056 --> 02:21.768
He cooks an interview.
He takes a pair of scissors to raw footage.

02:21.851 --> 02:23.269
Of a man on the street?

02:23.353 --> 02:25.730
Of a retired, three-star Marine general.

02:25.897 --> 02:28.858
We go to air.
48 hours it takes for the story to come undone

02:28.942 --> 02:30.276
and with it Atlantis Cable News.

02:30.360 --> 02:32.195
ACN is brought to its knees.

02:32.278 --> 02:35.198
The producer's surgical strike is
discovered and the producer is fired.

02:35.365 --> 02:36.991
Does he write an open letter
to the <i>New York Times,</i>

02:37.075 --> 02:38.660
apologizing to the public, his colleagues,

02:38.743 --> 02:40.787
the three-star general,
and the US Armed Forces?

02:40.870 --> 02:43.623
No, he sues us for wrongful termination.

02:43.873 --> 02:46.334
And I need to know,
I need some kind of sign from you, Rebecca,

02:46.417 --> 02:47.919
because you're obviously, all four of you,

02:48.086 --> 02:50.255
you can't be stupid
and afford haircuts this good.

02:50.338 --> 02:53.758
I need you to tell me
that this is exactly as insane as it is.

02:53.842 --> 02:56.219
I'm afraid I'm going to have to infuriate you.

02:56.886 --> 02:58.972
- Why?
- Because it is nuanced.

02:59.055 --> 03:02.016
He cooked an interview.
He took pruning shears to the raw...

03:02.100 --> 03:05.019
Rebecca, if he doused the studio in kerosene

03:05.103 --> 03:07.772
and lit a tiki torch, it wouldn't have
done as much damage as Genoa,

03:07.856 --> 03:10.441
so where is the complexity?
Where is the nuance?

03:10.984 --> 03:13.903
His claim is he's a scapegoat.

03:13.987 --> 03:15.280
- DON: That's his claim?
- Yeah.

03:15.572 --> 03:18.449
I understand why he'd feel that way,
because it was entirely his fault.

03:18.533 --> 03:21.452
And if it was entirely his fault,
then it's not at all anyone else's.

03:21.619 --> 03:22.954
It was not at all anyone else's.

03:23.037 --> 03:24.539
That's where the plaintiff disagrees.

03:24.622 --> 03:26.958
And if Dantana
was being offered as a sacrifice to the gods...

03:27.125 --> 03:29.752
- Oh, Rebecca.
- And it was an institutional failure

03:29.836 --> 03:31.880
- that led to the airing of Genoa...
- I'm gonna eat this table.

03:31.963 --> 03:36.050
And he is paying the price for
mistakes that were made above him.

03:36.175 --> 03:38.386
This isn't an original story, Don.

03:38.469 --> 03:40.471
- He cooked...
- That's the nuance.

03:40.555 --> 03:43.433
The nuance is he's gonna
leverage the public's inexhaustible love

03:43.516 --> 03:44.809
of big shots falling down.

03:45.101 --> 03:47.061
Charlie, Will, and Mac.

03:47.145 --> 03:48.563
I know how this ends.

03:48.646 --> 03:51.941
Why is it called a red team?

03:55.737 --> 03:57.864
- The blood cells.
- Hmm?

03:58.531 --> 04:00.950
White blood cells attack an infection,
red blood cells clean it up.

04:01.034 --> 04:03.620
You have a group of people
investigating a story, they're the white team.

04:03.703 --> 04:05.622
Other people are purposely
kept out of the loop

04:05.705 --> 04:07.248
so that when the white team
is ready, they can...

04:07.332 --> 04:09.250
- Fresh eyes.
- We're supposed to poke holes in it.

04:09.334 --> 04:11.085
- REBECCA: And were you able to?
- Were we...

04:11.169 --> 04:13.129
The first red team. You,

04:14.923 --> 04:17.175
Jim Harper, Sloan Sabbith.

04:17.258 --> 04:18.927
Was anyone able to poke holes in it?

04:19.260 --> 04:21.763
No. Other than the made-up interview,
it was a solid story.

04:21.846 --> 04:23.264
I'm just asking if you
were able to poke holes in it.

04:23.348 --> 04:25.099
This is exactly what I'm talking about.
What does it matter?

04:25.183 --> 04:26.434
It matters.

04:26.559 --> 04:29.520
It matters because
there were holes in the story, right?

04:29.604 --> 04:31.814
- Yeah.
- Now, Don, a ton of them, right?

04:31.898 --> 04:33.733
- We didn't see the holes because...
- REBECCA: Ah.

04:34.984 --> 04:36.861
That's institutional failure, right?

04:39.697 --> 04:41.240
You don't have to answer that. In fact, don't.

04:41.366 --> 04:42.575
I can.

04:42.659 --> 04:45.870
First red team meeting
was seven months ago.

04:45.954 --> 04:47.288
Charlie wants more evidence.

04:47.372 --> 04:50.458
Second red team meeting,
you have Stomtonovich now.

04:50.541 --> 04:53.002
- Charlie still wants more evidence.
- That's not diligent?

04:53.086 --> 04:55.088
Third red team meeting,
you have Valenzuela now

04:55.171 --> 04:56.839
and Charlie green-lights Genoa.

04:56.923 --> 04:59.467
And I'm asking you,
other than the cooked tape, Mrs. Lincoln,

04:59.550 --> 05:01.094
were there any holes in the story?

05:02.929 --> 05:04.722
- Yes.
- But you didn't find any of them.

05:04.806 --> 05:06.391
We found all of them.

05:06.641 --> 05:07.725
And I grant you it would've been better

05:07.809 --> 05:09.227
if we found them before the story aired.

05:09.310 --> 05:11.771
- You'll grant me that.
- He digitally remastered an interview.

05:11.854 --> 05:15.858
That is the all of it. That's it.
There was no institutional failure.

05:15.942 --> 05:17.568
Where was the third red team meeting?

05:17.902 --> 05:19.988
Where did Charlie give the green light?

05:21.322 --> 05:22.740
It was right in this room.

05:22.824 --> 05:26.202
This is an interview
with Gunnery Sergeant Eric Sweeney,

05:26.285 --> 05:28.997
the first member
of the Genoa crew to come forward.

05:29.080 --> 05:31.249
It was recorded in September of last year.

05:31.332 --> 05:33.459
The third red team meeting, red team three,

05:33.543 --> 05:36.337
we were all walked through
the evidence again.

05:36.421 --> 05:38.965
One, Jerry gets a tip from Cyrus West,

05:39.048 --> 05:41.551
a retired Air Force captain
who had just appeared on <i>News Night</i>

05:41.634 --> 05:42.760
in support of drone strikes.

05:43.011 --> 05:46.931
Cyrus West is known among people I know
as a guy with ambition.

05:47.015 --> 05:48.933
What kind of ambition?

05:49.017 --> 05:51.477
Congress, <i>Dancing With the Stars,</i>
I don't know.

05:51.602 --> 05:53.312
But you have to take
what he said with a salt lick.

05:53.604 --> 05:55.106
Did you warn anyone about that?

05:55.773 --> 05:57.275
I couldn't. I wasn't in the loop.

05:57.358 --> 05:58.943
You also weren't in New York.

05:59.027 --> 06:01.612
I was in New Hampshire
with the Romney campaign at the time.

06:01.696 --> 06:04.032
- Why?
- I was covering for our embed,

06:04.115 --> 06:05.867
a guy named Ben Furusho who'd hurt himself.

06:05.950 --> 06:07.368
- How'd he hurt himself?
- JIM: Ben?

06:07.452 --> 06:09.328
- Yeah.
- Mark is asking did he hurt himself

06:09.412 --> 06:11.122
saving people from a burning building?

06:11.289 --> 06:13.541
No, he got drunk and tried to jump

06:13.624 --> 06:16.419
from his second-floor balcony
into the pool at the Nashua Holiday Inn.

06:16.502 --> 06:19.422
KEN: Were you the only
one available to cover for him?

06:19.505 --> 06:20.631
No.

06:20.715 --> 06:22.675
Were you the only one
qualified to cover for him?

06:22.759 --> 06:23.760
JIM: No.

06:23.843 --> 06:25.511
Who made the decision
you should cover for him?

06:25.595 --> 06:28.389
- I did.
- ROSS: You sent yourself to New Hampshire?

06:28.473 --> 06:30.391
I think you know what
these guys are getting at.

06:35.313 --> 06:36.814
There is a woman I work with.

06:36.898 --> 06:39.942
Maggie Jordan.
We don't have to make this excruciating.

06:40.026 --> 06:41.527
You had a relationship with a coworker.

06:41.611 --> 06:42.612
It wasn't a relationship.

06:42.987 --> 06:44.363
You had something with Maggie,

06:44.447 --> 06:46.532
but she was living with Don
and your heart was a little dinged up,

06:46.616 --> 06:47.867
so you wanted to get out of town for a while

06:47.950 --> 06:49.744
and that's why you weren't
available to do your job,

06:49.827 --> 06:52.080
which at that moment
included saying to MacKenzie,

06:52.163 --> 06:54.040
"Don't trust Cyrus West."

06:54.540 --> 06:55.875
What is it Jerry's counting on?

06:55.958 --> 06:58.086
That you guys don't want
stories like that made public.

06:58.169 --> 06:59.295
Go back to red team three.

06:59.378 --> 07:01.297
Genoa got on the air
because I was distracted?

07:01.380 --> 07:02.381
Go back.

07:04.592 --> 07:09.388
One, Jerry gets the tip from Cyrus West.
The tip leads him to Eric Sweeney. That's two.

07:09.472 --> 07:10.515
JERRY: Here's the Sweeney interview.

07:11.474 --> 07:14.268
JERRY: <i>Would you say your</i>
<i>name, rank, and your last billet?</i>

07:14.352 --> 07:15.728
<i>Gunnery Sergeant Eric Sweeney.</i>

07:16.187 --> 07:19.148
<i>Before my discharge,</i>
<i>I was stationed with a MARSOC unit in J-bad.</i>

07:19.232 --> 07:21.776
JERRY: <i>That's Marine Special Operations</i>
<i>Command in Jalalabad?</i>

07:21.859 --> 07:23.236
ERIC: <i>Yes, sir.</i>

07:23.444 --> 07:26.030
JERRY: <i>Have you ever heard</i>
<i>of a black op called Genoa?</i>

07:26.114 --> 07:27.281
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

07:27.365 --> 07:29.700
JERRY: <i>Did you participate in that black op?</i>

07:29.784 --> 07:33.871
This was maybe the hundredth time
I'd seen the Sweeney interview.

07:33.996 --> 07:36.457
Intel had location on two Marine POWs

07:36.541 --> 07:38.960
who'd been separated
from their unit three days earlier

07:39.043 --> 07:41.337
during a firefight in the Hindu Kush.

07:41.462 --> 07:43.422
They'd been smuggled across the border

07:43.506 --> 07:45.633
and the Pakistani Taliban
intended to sell them

07:45.716 --> 07:47.009
for propaganda purposes.

07:47.093 --> 07:49.554
What does "propaganda purposes" mean?

07:49.679 --> 07:51.139
<i>They were gonna be publically beheaded.</i>

07:51.222 --> 07:53.599
<i>And if we didn't get them before they were</i>
<i>moved again, we'd lose them.</i>

07:53.683 --> 07:55.143
Operation Genoa was an extraction.

07:55.226 --> 07:57.395
A MARSOC unit flies in
on a couple of Black Hawks

07:57.478 --> 08:00.231
and grabs our guys,
but the first unit was overrun

08:00.314 --> 08:03.568
and the second unit, the story goes,

08:03.693 --> 08:05.069
dropped sarin gas.

08:05.153 --> 08:06.779
<i>Suddenly I'm tripping over people screaming.</i>

08:06.988 --> 08:09.574
<i>Boils and burns on their bodies.</i>
<i>Some of them passed out.</i>

08:09.657 --> 08:11.075
JERRY: <i>What did you think</i>
<i>was in the missile?</i>

08:11.159 --> 08:14.245
<i>I wasn't sure, but I didn't have time</i>
<i>to think about it until we were out of there.</i>

08:14.328 --> 08:16.789
<i>So later I'm talking to the crew,</i>
<i>I'm asking about the weapons package.</i>

08:16.873 --> 08:18.332
<i>Why'd the white phosphorus do that?</i>

08:18.416 --> 08:19.625
<i>And the guy said it wasn't the Willie Pete.</i>

08:19.709 --> 08:22.920
<i>I said, "What was it?" He said, "Sarin."</i>

08:23.504 --> 08:26.174
NEAL: <i>Will was the only one in the room</i>
<i>who hadn't heard the story before.</i>

08:26.716 --> 08:29.302
I looked over to see
what his first reaction was going to be.

08:29.385 --> 08:31.012
ERIC: <i>And the guy said</i>
<i>it wasn't the Willie Pete.</i>

08:31.095 --> 08:34.348
<i>I said, "What was it?" He said, "Sarin."</i>

08:34.432 --> 08:36.475
NEAL: <i>There was no expression.</i>

08:37.101 --> 08:39.270
Cyrus West, Eric Sweeney, that's one and two.

08:39.812 --> 08:41.689
The tweets from Hamni8 were three.

08:41.772 --> 08:43.733
Four was Leon Deit and the NGO report.

08:44.650 --> 08:47.445
Five was Charlie's source
who handed over the helo manifest.

08:47.528 --> 08:50.198
CHARLIE: This is a list of every
weapon the Black Hawks were carrying,

08:50.281 --> 08:52.867
or at least one of the two Black Hawks.

08:52.950 --> 08:54.118
MX-76.

08:54.952 --> 08:57.747
Five munitions experts
say there's no such thing.

08:57.830 --> 09:01.167
It's what you write in that spot when your
payload is codeword-classified.

09:01.292 --> 09:02.376
That's the sarin.

09:02.460 --> 09:04.670
Charlie's source
was our fifth piece of evidence.

09:04.754 --> 09:06.589
Were you happy with the evidence so far?

09:07.465 --> 09:09.258
- Was I?
- Yeah.

09:09.508 --> 09:10.509
(CHUCKLES)

09:10.927 --> 09:13.888
Rebecca, I run our website.
I'm not an investigative reporter.

09:13.971 --> 09:16.474
Yeah, I'm just asking
how you felt about the evidence so far.

09:18.643 --> 09:20.186
I'm not qualified to judge the evidence.

09:20.478 --> 09:22.021
You were on the Genoa team?

09:22.104 --> 09:23.397
- Yeah.
- You were put on the team?

09:23.481 --> 09:24.565
- Yes. Yes.
- Neal.

09:24.649 --> 09:25.733
Don't ever fucking say out loud

09:25.816 --> 09:27.318
that you are unqualified
to judge the evidence.

09:27.443 --> 09:28.694
- Wait...
- Don't ever say it again.

09:28.778 --> 09:31.155
I was absolutely qualified
to chase the Hamni8 tweets,

09:31.280 --> 09:33.824
- which was my job on the team.
- I get that. You get that.

09:34.075 --> 09:36.327
They get that. Let's quit while we're ahead.

09:37.411 --> 09:40.248
Five was Charlie's source
with the helo manifest.

09:40.581 --> 09:42.375
Six was Stomtonovich.

09:42.458 --> 09:45.419
JERRY: <i>At the time of Genoa,</i>
<i>we still had sarin gas. Is that right?</i>

09:45.503 --> 09:47.421
STOMTONOVICH: <i>Yes, we did.</i>
JERRY: <i>You're sure of this?</i>

09:47.630 --> 09:51.592
STOMTONOVICH: <i>We had sarin gas</i>
<i>at the time of Genoa and we have sarin today.</i>

09:51.676 --> 09:54.095
JERRY: <i>According to the OPCW,</i>
<i>the US was scheduled</i>

09:54.178 --> 09:57.348
<i>to have completed</i>
<i>its destruction of chemical weapons by 2007.</i>

09:57.431 --> 09:58.599
STOMTONOVICH:
<i>The US missed that deadline.</i>

09:58.683 --> 09:59.934
Stop the tape, please.

10:02.687 --> 10:04.021
What are we gonna do
about the basketball game?

10:04.480 --> 10:05.481
We'll blur it out.

10:05.564 --> 10:07.441
Why was the interview conducted
in front of a game?

10:07.525 --> 10:10.736
- He wanted it on.
- Why not move his chair?

10:10.820 --> 10:12.613
I wanted the Marine paraphernalia in the shot,

10:12.697 --> 10:14.532
but to get that,
I couldn't frame out the screen,

10:14.615 --> 10:17.118
which I knew I could take out later.
Is this important?

10:20.830 --> 10:22.540
NEAL: <i>Still no reaction from Will.</i>

10:22.873 --> 10:25.376
Stomtonovich was six
and then Valenzuela was seven.

10:25.459 --> 10:28.296
I conducted the interview with
Lance Corporal Herman Valenzuela

10:28.379 --> 10:31.382
on August 22, the day before yesterday.

10:31.507 --> 10:33.175
- Here it is.
- (KEYBOARD CLICKS)

10:33.259 --> 10:35.428
MACKENZIE: <i>Did you use gas on the mission?</i>

10:36.554 --> 10:38.264
SLOAN: Valenzuela, the crew chief on board

10:38.347 --> 10:41.225
one of the two MARSOC helos,
confirms everything we've been told by West,

10:41.350 --> 10:42.852
Sweeney, and Stomtonovich,

10:43.227 --> 10:45.980
all of which is consistent
with the tweets from Hamni8,

10:46.063 --> 10:49.066
the Leon Deit report
and Charlie's source with the helo manifest.

10:49.567 --> 10:51.027
The presentation is over

10:51.110 --> 10:53.404
and Will's just heard
everything for the first time.

10:53.487 --> 10:57.199
This is what's been happening
for the last 11 months.

10:57.283 --> 10:58.993
Yeah, I had a hunch.

10:59.577 --> 11:00.995
You did?

11:05.082 --> 11:06.542
I heard the same story.

11:11.422 --> 11:13.466
SLOAN: <i>That came as kind of a shock</i>
<i>to everybody.</i>

11:13.716 --> 11:16.177
Like Charlie's source,
Will was only able to identify

11:16.260 --> 11:18.846
him or her as reliable
and in a position to know.

11:18.929 --> 11:20.014
At that moment...

11:20.097 --> 11:22.016
I know what you're gonna ask
and it doesn't matter.

11:22.099 --> 11:24.352
Sloan, at that moment,
did anyone in the room...

11:24.435 --> 11:26.604
You've got everyone,
you've got the president of the news division,

11:26.687 --> 11:29.190
the editor and anchor in chief, the EP,

11:29.273 --> 11:30.983
- senior producer, staff.
- It didn't matter.

11:31.108 --> 11:33.235
Did anyone at that moment think to ask

11:33.319 --> 11:36.364
if Charlie's source
and Will's source were the same person?

11:37.656 --> 11:38.866
It didn't matter.

11:38.949 --> 11:40.201
- Did anyone...
- It was already a go.

11:40.284 --> 11:41.702
Will's source was just extra.

11:41.786 --> 11:45.289
It didn't make you feel more confident
that Will had heard it, too?

11:47.500 --> 11:49.627
- Yes.
- Did anyone ask?

11:51.587 --> 11:52.755
No.

11:54.840 --> 11:57.510
How many more times
did you review the evidence?

11:57.635 --> 11:58.677
I'm not sure.

11:58.761 --> 12:02.014
We went through
the whole thing maybe four more times.

12:02.139 --> 12:03.307
I'm ready to say go.

12:04.141 --> 12:05.851
You know how I feel.

12:05.935 --> 12:06.977
- I'm convinced.
- I'm not.

12:07.061 --> 12:08.062
- I know.
- Mac.

12:08.145 --> 12:09.647
Tell me why.

12:11.607 --> 12:12.900
It just doesn't feel right.

12:13.067 --> 12:15.861
11 months of reporting versus your gut?
I'll take the reporting.

12:16.028 --> 12:18.447
- I'd take Jim's gut.
- Me, too.

12:18.531 --> 12:20.491
You worship at the altar of logic and reason.

12:20.783 --> 12:23.494
And I don't believe this many people
could keep something like this a secret.

12:23.577 --> 12:25.454
- Well, they didn't.
- Jerry, I know these guys.

12:25.538 --> 12:28.416
Due respect, Jim,
but you fetishize these guys.

12:28.791 --> 12:30.709
Two million men and women
in the armed services.

12:30.835 --> 12:32.336
You were embedded with a couple of units.

12:32.420 --> 12:34.296
- You know a few of these guys.
- Hang on.

12:34.380 --> 12:36.424
I don't think it's fetishizing to admire people

12:36.507 --> 12:38.551
who signed up to fight
a couple of wars that neither one of us

12:38.634 --> 12:41.262
wanted to dirty our hands with,
but I do give them the benefit of the doubt.

12:41.345 --> 12:43.347
I gave them the benefit of the doubt, too,
until I saw pictures

12:43.431 --> 12:45.266
of what's-her-name doing the "get this" pose

12:45.349 --> 12:48.310
next to prisoners in dog collars
wired to car batteries.

12:48.394 --> 12:49.603
It doesn't feel right?

12:49.687 --> 12:53.065
We've tortured, drowned, wiretapped,
renditioned, and suspended due process,

12:53.190 --> 12:55.985
but you think we drew a moral
and legal line someplace?

12:56.068 --> 12:57.778
- Are you one of the Andrews Sisters?
- MACKENZIE: All right.

12:57.862 --> 12:59.113
It doesn't feel right because...

12:59.196 --> 13:01.115
