16:28.072 --> 16:31.075
HERB: Ready 17. Stand by 19 through 22A.

16:31.659 --> 16:32.743
Standing.

16:32.951 --> 16:35.120
<i>But we sat down with</i>
<i>a Marine three-star general,</i>

16:35.245 --> 16:38.707
<i>an expert in chemical weapons</i>
<i>with knowledge of Operation Genoa.</i>

16:39.083 --> 16:42.127
<i>At his request, we blacked out his face</i>
<i>and electronically altered his voice.</i>

16:42.211 --> 16:43.212
HERB: Go 17.

16:43.671 --> 16:45.005
JERRY: <i>According to the OPCW,</i>

16:45.089 --> 16:47.132
<i>the US was scheduled to have</i>
<i>completed its destruction</i>

16:47.216 --> 16:49.218
<i>of chemical weapons by 2007.</i>

16:49.301 --> 16:51.053
STOMTONOVICH:
<i>The US missed that deadline.</i>

16:51.136 --> 16:54.682
<i>They extended it to 2012</i>
<i>and they missed that deadline, too.</i>

16:54.807 --> 16:57.976
<i>At the time of Genoa,</i>
<i>we destroyed at least 87%...</i>

16:58.102 --> 17:01.355
<i>We asked if any exceptional</i>
<i>measures were used in the operation.</i>

17:01.438 --> 17:04.566
STOMTONOVICH:
<i>Exceptional measures were called for.</i>

17:04.733 --> 17:07.152
WILL: <i>We asked if sarin gas was used.</i>

17:08.278 --> 17:09.905
STOMTONOVICH: <i>We used sarin.</i>

17:10.364 --> 17:12.408
WILL: <i>A crew chief from the operation</i>
<i>speaks to us</i>

17:12.491 --> 17:15.244
<i>when</i> ACN Reports <i>returns right after this.</i>

17:32.845 --> 17:34.638
<i>What are your duties as crew chief?</i>

17:34.722 --> 17:36.807
<i>I'm in charge of the crew and the equipment.</i>

17:36.890 --> 17:39.143
<i>Do you oversee the loading</i>
<i>of the helicopter, the payload?</i>

17:39.560 --> 17:42.813
<i>Yes, during preflight,</i>
<i>I'd be responsible for the payload.</i>

17:50.571 --> 17:52.489
(INAUDIBLE)

18:20.517 --> 18:23.937
<i>...being roughly 7,500 tons of sarin.</i>

18:24.104 --> 18:27.107
The Pentagon declined
our request for an interview.

18:27.191 --> 18:31.278
For everyone at <i>ACN Reports,</i>
I'm Will McAvoy. Good night.

18:38.494 --> 18:39.995
Are you here for a call?

18:40.078 --> 18:42.039
Congratulations?

18:42.122 --> 18:45.375
General Stomtonovich.
Charlie, he's screaming.

18:50.130 --> 18:52.216
He says he never said they used sarin.

18:52.299 --> 18:53.300
It's on film.

18:53.425 --> 18:55.594
- He says he never said that.
- It's on film.

18:56.011 --> 18:58.180
- I knew this would happen.
- It happens all the time.

18:58.263 --> 19:01.683
These guys get cold feet
or someone at the DOD begs them to recant.

19:01.767 --> 19:02.768
What's he saying we did?

19:03.060 --> 19:04.311
Edited him out of context.

19:04.394 --> 19:06.146
- Did you tell him we have the raw footage?
- Yeah.

19:06.230 --> 19:08.273
Raw footage isn't edited out of context.

19:08.357 --> 19:10.150
- It isn't edited at all.
- CHARLIE: I told him that.

19:10.234 --> 19:13.028
- What did he say?
- He said he was gonna kill me.

19:13.195 --> 19:15.697
Did he say it the way Mac says it to me
or did it seem like he meant it?

19:15.823 --> 19:18.242
- I mean it when I say it to you.
- CHARLIE: He was very upset.

19:18.325 --> 19:20.410
Tell him I'm gonna go right now
to look at the raw interview again

19:20.494 --> 19:22.287
and that he can look at it with me if he wants.

19:22.746 --> 19:23.914
All right.

19:23.997 --> 19:26.124
- We knew things were gonna happen.
- MACKENZIE: Yeah.

19:26.250 --> 19:30.504
Chemical weapons expert wants to kill me.
I make the worst enemies.

19:30.587 --> 19:33.131
Seriously, I'm a perfectly nice guy.

19:33.423 --> 19:34.842
(EXCITED CHATTER)

19:35.425 --> 19:36.677
People are celebrating out there.

19:36.760 --> 19:39.555
- Yeah, I'm coming out.
- Who's playing?

19:39.763 --> 19:42.224
WILL: The California Golden Bears
are hosting the UCLA Bruins.

19:43.517 --> 19:44.810
You'll watch anything, won't you?

19:45.435 --> 19:46.520
Yeah.

19:50.107 --> 19:51.316
MACKENZIE: Why are there two clocks?

19:52.943 --> 19:54.736
One's the game clock
and one's the play clock.

19:54.820 --> 19:56.864
The game clock is showing
how much time is left in the quarter

19:56.947 --> 19:59.575
and the play clock shows
how much time is left to get off the play.

19:59.658 --> 20:01.535
They only have a certain amount of
time to complete the play?

20:01.618 --> 20:03.704
They only have a certain amount of time
to start the play.

20:04.413 --> 20:05.706
Don't have that rule in soccer.

20:05.789 --> 20:07.207
They don't have any rules in soccer.

20:07.291 --> 20:09.376
That's why you think a game
that ends in a zero-zero tie

20:09.459 --> 20:10.711
- is a gamely fought match.
- It's called nil-nil.

20:10.794 --> 20:12.588
I was trying to keep it from being worse.

20:12.671 --> 20:13.922
I was helping you out.

20:15.340 --> 20:19.094
Do any other sports have enforced pacing?
Does baseball?

20:19.219 --> 20:22.347
No, pitchers commonly
go for a sandwich between pitches.

20:25.350 --> 20:27.394
Golf, you can be penalized for slow play.

20:27.477 --> 20:30.647
Hockey, you can hang onto the puck
for as long as you want,

20:30.731 --> 20:33.025
but before too long a guy
named Lars is gonna hurt you.

20:33.108 --> 20:36.445
Basketball has a shot clock.
You've got 24 seconds

20:36.528 --> 20:38.447
to put up a shot, or in college it's 35.

20:38.530 --> 20:40.282
Tennis, you can lose a point for slow play.

20:40.365 --> 20:41.575
- Listen.
- Yeah.

20:41.658 --> 20:43.785
Should we be worried about
the Stomtonovich call?

20:44.661 --> 20:46.997
- It's on film.
- Okay.

20:47.331 --> 20:49.917
I'm gonna look at it again now.

20:50.000 --> 20:52.002
Go Bruins! Beat the Golden Bears.

20:52.085 --> 20:55.339
Beat them as hard as you can.
Beat them with impunity!

20:55.422 --> 20:58.133
- You have no idea what you're saying.
- MACKENZIE: I know.

21:00.510 --> 21:02.804
- DON: We thought the DOD would have...
- I thought.

21:04.264 --> 21:08.852
I thought the DOD would have a response
on their website by midnight.

21:08.977 --> 21:11.313
But by 6:00 a.m.
we hadn't heard anything yet.

21:11.396 --> 21:12.940
- (KNOCKING ON DOOR)
- Come on in.

21:13.065 --> 21:15.025
Excuse me.

21:18.153 --> 21:20.322
- You guys have met?
- We have.

21:20.405 --> 21:22.157
- How are you?
- Good, thank you.

21:25.535 --> 21:27.788
She says she never heard
Stomtonovich say it happened.

21:27.913 --> 21:29.873
- Then that's what it is.
- Even in her condition?

21:29.957 --> 21:32.793
- Hmm?
- You'd take her word for it in her condition?

21:32.876 --> 21:34.920
In the condition she was in
when they did the interview?

21:35.003 --> 21:38.131
She's not in a condition,
and yes, I'd take her word for it.

21:38.215 --> 21:39.967
If she wasn't sure, she'd say she wasn't sure.

21:40.050 --> 21:42.844
On the witness stand,
that's not gonna sound like honorable loyalty.

21:42.928 --> 21:44.554
It's gonna sound like you're
willing to believe anybody

21:44.680 --> 21:45.681
as long as you slept with them.

