This is the very last polling data
taken before the polls open tomorrow.

21:51.478 --> 21:52.813
Who's gonna win?

21:53.230 --> 21:54.856
The President will be reelected.

21:54.940 --> 21:57.484
But Tulsi Gabbard's gonna
win in Hawaii's second.

21:57.567 --> 21:59.236
She'll be the first Samoan in Congress.

21:59.361 --> 22:03.949
And Kerry Bentivolio is gonna take the seat
vacated by Thaddeus McCotter,

22:04.074 --> 22:07.494
who came out with my pick
for the best resignation statement of all time.

22:08.412 --> 22:11.623
"The recent event's totalities of
calumnies, indignities and deceits

22:11.707 --> 22:13.583
"have weighed most heavily upon my family.

22:13.667 --> 22:16.420
"Thus, acutely aware
one cannot rebuild their hearth

22:16.503 --> 22:18.839
"among the ruins of their US House office,

22:18.922 --> 22:21.591
"for the sake of my loved ones,
I must strike another match,

22:21.675 --> 22:24.636
"go start anew by embracing the promotion

22:24.761 --> 22:27.139
"back from public servant
to sovereign citizen."

22:28.557 --> 22:30.517
Sounds like he and his friends
Rosencrantz and Guildenstern

22:30.600 --> 22:34.646
are about to take a journey by sea to ask the
Duke of Verona for his most kind blessing.

22:34.771 --> 22:36.023
(LAUGHS)

22:36.106 --> 22:37.441
I like you, Keefer.

22:37.858 --> 22:39.359
My trust in Maggie

22:40.193 --> 22:42.612
has nothing to do with anything
but the right things.

22:43.989 --> 22:46.450
6:00 a.m., you hadn't heard from the DOD.

22:46.575 --> 22:48.452
7:00 a.m., 8:00 a.m., nothing.

22:48.535 --> 22:50.704
- REBECCA: Maybe they hadn't seen the show.
- They see the Internet.

22:50.787 --> 22:52.205
This was Monday morning, September 10.

22:52.289 --> 22:53.457
DON: Yeah.

22:54.541 --> 22:56.251
You had another story creeping up on you.

22:56.710 --> 22:58.253
Nobody knew that yet.

22:59.087 --> 23:01.673
Everybody below the producer level
has to take a shift doing the book.

23:01.798 --> 23:03.592
That morning it was Neal's turn.

23:03.675 --> 23:04.968
What's the book?

23:05.469 --> 23:07.554
- KENDRA: Neal.
- (SIGHS)

23:07.929 --> 23:10.057
NEAL: It seems like it's my turn
more often than it should be.

23:10.140 --> 23:11.224
Man up.

23:11.308 --> 23:12.851
I'm always manned up.
That's my default mode.

23:12.934 --> 23:14.227
Then go into ultra man mode.

23:14.311 --> 23:16.563
The women here couldn't deal
with my ultra man mode.

23:16.646 --> 23:18.356
Probably not. Are you gonna take this?

23:18.440 --> 23:19.441
- It's heavy.
- (SIGHS)

