Sponsored by HeartBlast,

25:34.117 --> 25:36.244
a new defibrillator company
from the people who brought you...

25:36.328 --> 25:38.955
Piers Morgan and Rihanna
had a Twitter fight about her haircut.

25:39.039 --> 25:41.333
I'll give you $100 if you go pitch that to Will.

25:41.416 --> 25:44.085
I know you're not gonna
think this one's important, but it is.

25:44.169 --> 25:45.503
<i>- Star Magazine...</i>
- Nope.

25:45.587 --> 25:48.715
...is reporting that a palace source confirmed
that Kate Middleton is pregnant.

25:48.798 --> 25:51.885
- That's news I want to hear.
- You just did. Anything else?

25:52.636 --> 25:54.221
Lady Gaga showed a lot of cleavage

25:54.304 --> 25:57.057
- at an after-party for the Paralympic Games.
- Put that one aside.

25:57.140 --> 26:00.477
- Oh, and Terry Jones the Florida pastor?
- Yeah.

26:00.560 --> 26:03.897
He's screening the trailer to a movie
called <i>Innocence of Muslims.</i>

26:03.980 --> 26:05.482
- We thought...
- REBECCA: I thought.

26:07.943 --> 26:10.111
I thought, everyone thought

26:10.195 --> 26:12.739
that when the DOD posted its response,
it would be vague.

26:13.448 --> 26:15.700
"Pentagon doesn't comment
on classified operations,

26:15.784 --> 26:17.702
"but we have serious problems with the story

26:17.827 --> 26:20.497
"aired by Atlantis Cable News last night."
Something like that.

26:20.914 --> 26:23.667
You know the reason it was
taking them so long to respond?

26:24.042 --> 26:25.168
No.

26:25.252 --> 26:27.587
They were bringing a lawyer
into the Pentagon press office.

26:27.879 --> 26:31.007
- Pentagon counsel?
- And another lawyer.

26:31.132 --> 26:32.342
Matlock?

26:32.425 --> 26:35.387
The Attorney General.
They weren't fucking around.

26:42.811 --> 26:43.812
(COMPUTER CHIMES)

27:09.963 --> 27:11.548
We knew there'd be pushback.

27:16.177 --> 27:17.929
SLOAN: <i>But not like that.</i>

27:18.346 --> 27:20.682
"We are considering any
and all legal remedies

27:20.765 --> 27:23.727
"available to us including
under the Espionage Act.

27:24.394 --> 27:27.480
"In the interim, we will begin
declassifying documents

27:27.564 --> 27:29.899
"to prove the falsity of ACN's claims."

27:30.191 --> 27:33.695
If I'm a lawyer in that room,
I don't write that response unless I'm sure.

27:33.778 --> 27:34.904
We were sure.

27:35.447 --> 27:37.157
Still? It's noon, Monday.

27:38.116 --> 27:40.702
Charlie got everyone together
in the conference room.

27:40.785 --> 27:43.788
<i>He polled everyone to see</i>
<i>if they were still standing by the story.</i>

27:56.176 --> 27:58.720
<i>People were resolved.</i>

27:58.803 --> 28:00.680
<i>Jim had already said his piece.</i>

28:00.764 --> 28:03.183
<i>His job was to support Mac now,</i>
<i>and that's what he was doing.</i>

28:03.266 --> 28:05.060
REBECCA: <i>At the expense of good advice?</i>

28:05.435 --> 28:06.853
He'd given his advice.

28:06.936 --> 28:09.606
And Charlie, Mac, and Will
had given their instructions.

28:09.689 --> 28:11.858
Of course they pushed back.
What do we expect them to...

28:11.941 --> 28:14.611
"Well, you caught us. Bravo to you, sirs.

28:14.694 --> 28:16.613
"We'll walk ourselves
over to Leavenworth now."

28:17.864 --> 28:20.909
You know at some point at Little Bighorn,
I'll bet Custer led a unanimous vote

28:20.992 --> 28:23.161
where everyone said,
"I still think we can win."

28:23.286 --> 28:25.455
Then came Elliot's show that night.

28:25.580 --> 28:27.791
You know, Elliot was really
the only guy on the team

28:27.916 --> 28:30.377
who hadn't gotten dirty with Genoa yet.

28:30.460 --> 28:32.128
So we dropped dirt on him.

28:32.212 --> 28:33.588
Go.

28:33.671 --> 28:35.340
SLOAN: <i>The second MARSOC team</i>
<i>dropped sarin?</i>

28:35.423 --> 28:37.050
<i>- Yes.</i>
- SLOAN: <i>You're sure?</i>

28:37.133 --> 28:39.427
<i>- Yes.</i>
<i>- That's why you wore the MOPP suits?</i>

28:39.511 --> 28:42.263
<i>That's why we wore the MOPP suits</i>
<i>and that's why civilians died.</i>

28:42.347 --> 28:45.100
ELLIOT: <i>That was another clip from</i>
<i>last night's</i> ACN Reports,

28:45.183 --> 28:48.686
the startling and provocative story
of the extraction of two captured Marines.

28:49.104 --> 28:51.022
<i>Joining us by satellite</i>
<i>from Trenton, New Jersey,</i>

28:51.106 --> 28:53.650
<i>is former Marine Gunnery Sergeant</i>
<i>Eric Sweeney,</i>

28:53.775 --> 28:56.236
<i>a member of the MARSOC team</i>
<i>that executed the extraction,</i>

28:56.319 --> 28:57.404
<i>which was codenamed Genoa,</i>

28:57.487 --> 29:01.282
<i>and I should say the first member of the team</i>
<i>to step forward and tell his story.</i>

29:01.366 --> 29:02.742
<i>- Welcome, Mr. Sweeney.</i>
<i>- Thank you.</i>

29:02.826 --> 29:05.662
Let's start there. What made you come
forward and speak to the press?

29:05.787 --> 29:08.415
<i>I wish I could say it was honorable.</i>
<i>It was a guilty conscience.</i>

29:08.498 --> 29:10.208
- Guilty that...
<i>- I knew what we'd done.</i>

29:10.792 --> 29:13.878
"Any and all legal remedies."
Is that something they usually say?

29:13.962 --> 29:16.005
DON: They said it when the SEAL
released his bin Laden book.

29:16.089 --> 29:18.550
- They haven't charged him.
- The Espionage Act?

29:18.716 --> 29:21.511
Do you know how many journalists have ever
been tried under the Espionage Act?

29:21.594 --> 29:22.846
- None.
- Good.

29:23.179 --> 29:24.848
'Cause you wouldn't make it in jail, Don.

29:24.931 --> 29:28.435
I'd survive, but you wouldn't.
In fact, I'd thrive.

29:28.518 --> 29:29.602
How do you figure?

29:29.686 --> 29:31.396
<i>- Shawshank.</i>
- (LAUGHS)

29:32.272 --> 29:34.149
I'd do everybody's taxes
and invest the warden's money.

29:34.566 --> 29:36.568
What are you gonna do?
Produce their nightly news show?

29:36.693 --> 29:39.446
- Is this our sound or his?
- His. We're good.

29:39.529 --> 29:40.822
ERIC: <i>We want to be a force multiplier</i>

29:40.905 --> 29:42.907
<i>where one of us</i>
<i>can do the work of several infantrymen.</i>

29:42.991 --> 29:47.162
"The charge that US Special Operations
used sarin gas is absolutely false."

29:47.245 --> 29:50.874
I don't know. Absolutely?
Why not just say "false"?

29:50.957 --> 29:52.625
"Absolutely" sounds like
the kind of word you use...

29:52.709 --> 29:54.711
This isn't like the time
Chip left you a message in eighth grade

29:54.794 --> 29:57.881
and you and your friends did a lab analysis
to figure out if it meant he liked you.

30:00.800 --> 30:03.344
Chet was his name

30:03.428 --> 30:05.805
and sometimes boys are vague
with their messages.

30:05.889 --> 30:07.140
ELLIOT: <i>Was that the first time</i>

30:07.223 --> 30:09.100
<i>that you had to perform a medical procedure</i>
<i>in action?</i>

30:09.893 --> 30:11.102
Move him back to Genoa when you can.

30:11.227 --> 30:13.980
<i>We have advanced combat medicine</i>
<i>as part of our training.</i>

30:14.063 --> 30:17.066
<i>The first time I had to use it, we were</i>
<i>on a mission to pay some tribal leaders...</i>

30:17.150 --> 30:18.693
I don't know what he's talking about anymore.

30:18.776 --> 30:21.446
<i>We hit two IEDs and my Humvee blew apart</i>

30:21.571 --> 30:24.073
<i>and three of us sustained TBIs,</i>
<i>traumatic brain injuries.</i>

30:24.449 --> 30:26.201
<i>And I was dragging a friend of mine...</i>

30:26.284 --> 30:28.119
Did he say "us"?

30:28.745 --> 30:31.664
He said "the three of us."
Traumatic brain injury. He said that.

30:31.748 --> 30:32.874
- TBI?
- I heard it.

30:32.957 --> 30:35.293
Sergeant, did you say that you
sustained a traumatic brain injury?

30:36.377 --> 30:38.630
- Well, it wasn't serious.
- Get out.

30:38.713 --> 30:41.591
<i>- Did you disclose that information to the...</i>
- Get out!

30:41.674 --> 30:43.426
Okay, we've got to go to break,

30:43.885 --> 30:48.515
<i>but we're coming back with Eric Sweeney,</i>
<i>a MARSOC on Operation Genoa.</i>

30:48.598 --> 30:50.308
<i>This is</i> Right Now.

30:57.273 --> 30:59.275
(DISTANT SIREN WAILING)

31:04.614 --> 31:06.533
(RINGING)

31:08.409 --> 31:09.702
I saw it.

31:11.162 --> 31:13.748
There's a problem with the story.

31:13.831 --> 31:15.500
WILL: <i>I know.</i>

31:20.171 --> 31:21.756
(PEOPLE MURMURING)

31:24.842 --> 31:26.344
All right.

31:27.011 --> 31:28.680
Thank you for coming
in the middle of the night.

31:28.805 --> 31:31.766
And I'm sorry I'm late.
There was a deer on the Merritt Parkway.

31:32.100 --> 31:34.394
The deer ran across
and the car two in front of me hit it.

31:34.477 --> 31:36.771
- Was everyone all right?
- Yeah.

31:37.146 --> 31:38.231
Mac.

31:38.982 --> 31:40.191
Why didn't we know about the TBI?

31:40.275 --> 31:42.235
Everybody listen, okay?
Believe me, I cornered him...

31:42.318 --> 31:43.987
We knew he had two Purple Hearts.

31:44.070 --> 31:45.822
I got him on the phone in Trenton as soon...

31:45.905 --> 31:49.075
Just back up. We'll do this step by step.
He had two Purple Hearts.

31:49.158 --> 31:50.952
The medical information
is sealed and classified.

31:51.035 --> 31:53.830
He told us one is for a shrapnel wound
in his left shoulder

31:53.913 --> 31:56.374
sustained during an ambush
during his first tour in '08.

31:56.457 --> 31:58.376
- The second is...
- The second, he told us,

31:58.501 --> 32:00.670
was for a stab wound
in his leg he got while trying

32:00.753 --> 32:03.631
to subdue an angry teenage militant
in Kapisa Province.

32:03.715 --> 32:05.091
That's the one he was lying about.

32:05.174 --> 32:07.176
The second Purple Heart was for the TBI.

32:07.260 --> 32:09.721
- He showed us the knife wound.
- I asked him about that, too.

32:09.846 --> 32:11.764
He got it in his kitchen trying to open a CD.

32:12.223 --> 32:17.103
He didn't tell us about the TBI
because he didn't think we'd believe his story.

32:17.186 --> 32:18.771
JIM: Isn't that another way of saying

32:18.855 --> 32:21.357
he wanted to tell the Genoa story
so badly he lied?

32:21.441 --> 32:23.985
Well, so why would he lie
about a story that wasn't true?

32:24.068 --> 32:25.695
What's the biggest effect of a TBI?

32:25.862 --> 32:28.531
- I get that it's memory loss.
- It's memory loss.

32:28.656 --> 32:30.742
And it's dizziness and speech deficits.

32:30.825 --> 32:33.453
We didn't see any of those
in the hundred hours we spent with him.

32:33.536 --> 32:35.163
I don't understand.
So at least he doesn't have

32:35.246 --> 32:36.914
all the symptoms of a traumatic brain injury?

32:36.998 --> 32:41.085
GI Jim, what percentage of soldiers
taken to Walter Reed have a TBI?

32:41.169 --> 32:42.587
- A lot.
- It's 30%.

32:42.670 --> 32:45.048
So we're not gonna listen
to a third of wounded vets?

32:45.131 --> 32:47.592
We made this one a key witness
in an accusation of murder.

32:47.800 --> 32:49.010
He lied about an injury

32:49.093 --> 32:51.262
and the injury's number one symptom
is memory loss.

32:51.346 --> 32:52.347
Bring him up from Trenton.

32:55.350 --> 32:57.769
I'll do a pre-interview myself
and if I'm satisfied,

32:57.852 --> 33:00.396
I can put him through a direct examination
on the air and clean this up.

33:00.480 --> 33:03.775
Yeah, and can I just remind everybody
Sweeney's not our only witness.

33:03.900 --> 33:05.526
We've got Stomtonovich and Valenzuela.

33:05.610 --> 33:08.988
Two more witnesses, only 50% of whom
are recanting what they said.

33:09.072 --> 33:10.573
Stomtonovich can recant all he wants.

33:10.657 --> 33:12.784
We have the unedited tape
and Jerry and Maggie were there.

33:12.950 --> 33:13.951
Mmm-hmm.

33:14.118 --> 33:15.703
For the record, I wasn't.

33:15.995 --> 33:17.121
Wasn't what?

33:19.540 --> 33:21.668
I was sent out of the room
before the interview started.

33:21.751 --> 33:23.753
- Good. Let's get it all out now.
- Why?

33:23.920 --> 33:25.922
You and Charlie told him
it was going to be Jerry.

33:26.047 --> 33:27.882
You didn't tell him an AP was coming along.

33:27.965 --> 33:31.094
He had had me investigated, but not Maggie,
so he didn't feel comfortable...

33:31.177 --> 33:33.262
- You were the only one in the room with him?
- Yeah, I was.

33:33.346 --> 33:35.014
- And I see what's happening here.
- Nothing's happening.

33:35.098 --> 33:36.265
Can I bring something else up?

33:36.349 --> 33:39.644
We aired the story 27 hours ago,
so, yeah, now's the time.

33:40.019 --> 33:41.521
We aborted the interview
with Sweeney tonight.

33:41.604 --> 33:43.064
- I did.
- Uh, I did.

33:43.147 --> 33:44.732
- Should you have?
- I don't know.

33:44.816 --> 33:46.901
I was suddenly in a position
where I was asking questions

33:46.984 --> 33:49.195
I didn't know the answers to
about our own story.

33:49.278 --> 33:51.489
If it hadn't been our own story,
wouldn't you have kept going?

33:52.073 --> 33:53.491
"Did you disclose that
to the Genoa producers?

33:53.825 --> 33:57.120
"No? You lied? How has a TBI for which
you received a Purple Heart..."

33:57.203 --> 33:59.747
Yes, he would have kept going.
I shut him down.

33:59.831 --> 34:01.457
- It was live air.
- That doesn't make us look great.

34:01.541 --> 34:03.835
Looking great wasn't
one of their options right then.

34:03.918 --> 34:06.462
Everybody knock it off!

34:06.629 --> 34:08.548
Sister Mary Mother of God.

34:08.631 --> 34:11.884
We have a problem. That's all it is.

34:11.968 --> 34:14.387
We're not gonna have a fucking scrum!

34:16.139 --> 34:19.225
What do we have? What?

34:19.475 --> 34:22.895
A retired Marine general
started getting calls from his buddies.

34:22.979 --> 34:24.397
"What the hell is going on?"

34:24.480 --> 34:26.107
His voice was altered. His face was blacked.

34:26.190 --> 34:29.152
There are six people
who have the information he has

34:29.277 --> 34:31.487
and generals don't have dumb friends.

34:31.571 --> 34:32.989
What else?

34:33.114 --> 34:34.741
A witness who once had a concussion.

34:34.824 --> 34:36.492
- While saving other people's lives.
- CHARLIE: Thank you.

34:36.576 --> 34:40.329
- That's not...
- Jim, while being courageous.

34:40.413 --> 34:43.374
And he was courageous again
stepping forward.

34:43.875 --> 34:47.503
Kids used to lie about their age
to get in the Army and fight in a war.

34:47.587 --> 34:48.921
That's what Sweeney did here.

34:49.005 --> 34:50.757
How much of what you're saying
do you believe right now?

34:50.923 --> 34:52.008
60%.

34:52.175 --> 34:54.093
I thought it was in the mid-80s.
You pulled it off.

34:54.177 --> 34:55.511
Experience.

34:55.970 --> 34:57.180
You need to talk to Deep Throat.

34:57.263 --> 34:59.056
I'm on the first shuttle to Washington.

34:59.140 --> 35:01.851
- Have you talked to him on the phone?
- We don't talk on phones.

35:01.934 --> 35:03.603
- How about your guy?
- We talk on phones.

35:03.686 --> 35:04.771
He's asking have you talked to your guy?

35:05.563 --> 35:07.482
- An hour ago.
- MACKENZIE: And?

35:07.565 --> 35:09.817
He says stand by the story.

35:15.865 --> 35:18.075
We go back over every inch
starting right now.

35:18.284 --> 35:20.745
By 8:00 tonight,
I want Will to be able to say we stand by it.

35:20.828 --> 35:23.331
And when he says it, we stand by it.

35:23.498 --> 35:25.500
Break 'em into teams.

35:30.046 --> 35:32.715
Had you realized yet
at the time of that meeting

35:32.840 --> 35:34.884
that Sweeney and Stomtonovich
weren't your only problem?

35:35.134 --> 35:36.677
Who says they weren't our only problem?

35:36.761 --> 35:39.680
Right.
That was an example of a leading question.

35:40.056 --> 35:43.392
A leading question suggests its own answer.

35:43.476 --> 35:45.436
When did you stop beating your wife, right?

35:45.561 --> 35:47.063
We never established I beat my wife.

35:47.146 --> 35:48.940
We never established you're married.

35:49.023 --> 35:50.107
- I'm not.
- Yeah.

35:50.399 --> 35:52.235
I'm not following you, Rebecca.

35:52.401 --> 35:55.321
MacKenzie had realized
at the time of the meeting

35:55.446 --> 35:56.906
- that Sweeney and Stomtonovich...
- There's no way.

35:56.989 --> 35:58.741
- There's no way.
- Jim, listen to me.

35:58.825 --> 36:01.828
- There's no way Mac's to blame for this.
- Valenzuela was your third witness.

36:01.911 --> 36:04.580
I have seen lawyers do some things in my life.
Jesus.

36:04.747 --> 36:06.374
Just listen.

36:06.541 --> 36:09.585
First red team, you have Sweeney,
you don't go to air.

36:09.752 --> 36:13.089
Red team two, you have Sweeney and
Stomtonovich, you don't go to air.

36:13.172 --> 36:18.010
Red team three, you have Valenzuela now
and Charlie green-lights it.

36:18.261 --> 36:22.098
Valenzuela was an important witness.

36:23.057 --> 36:24.267
Yeah.

36:25.393 --> 36:26.686
And?

36:28.479 --> 36:29.814
What if I led him?

36:29.897 --> 36:31.774
- WILL: Valenzuela?
- In his pre-interview.

36:31.858 --> 36:33.818
I've read the pre-interview transcript
100 times.

36:33.943 --> 36:36.279
I read it 1,000 times, but I've just read it again

36:36.404 --> 36:38.781
and I have to wonder
if I inadvertently led on that witness.

36:38.948 --> 36:40.825
- You didn't.
- I can make the case that I did.

36:40.908 --> 36:42.243
Look at what's good on the story.

36:42.326 --> 36:45.955
Stomtonovich, he didn't like the report.
Sorry, but we've got him on film.

36:46.080 --> 36:47.707
Sweeney, he wants to be heard

36:47.790 --> 36:50.293
and he thinks he'll be discounted
'cause of the TBI, so he lies.

36:50.418 --> 36:52.628
And by the way,
if I had a traumatic brain injury

36:52.795 --> 36:54.505
and knew that information
couldn't be discovered

36:54.589 --> 36:57.466
unless I volunteered it, I wouldn't volunteer it.

36:57.592 --> 37:00.928
I have a source. Is it POTUS? No. It's better.

37:01.012 --> 37:02.388
What would it take for you
to tell me the source?

37:02.471 --> 37:04.056
Someone would have to be torturing you.

37:04.140 --> 37:05.683
That's sweet, but...

37:05.766 --> 37:08.311
- Charlie has a source. You trust Charlie?
- Of course.

37:08.436 --> 37:09.896
And we have Valenzuela.

37:09.979 --> 37:11.731
There is much more about
this story that's good...

37:11.856 --> 37:13.190
And I'm saying what if I led Valenzuela?

37:13.274 --> 37:15.568
I objected to that in courtrooms for years.

37:15.651 --> 37:17.445
I know what a leading question sounds like.

37:17.528 --> 37:18.613
Then you know I asked them.

37:18.696 --> 37:20.072
You have to ask them in these situations.

37:20.197 --> 37:22.575
The guy... He was reluctant.
He didn't want to talk.

37:22.658 --> 37:25.036
Read the first line on page three.

37:27.079 --> 37:31.459
"McHale: We have a three-star general
who's an expert in chemical weapons."

37:31.542 --> 37:34.170
MACKENZIE: We have a three-star general
who's an expert in chemical weapons.

37:34.253 --> 37:35.588
Do you think he's lying?

37:45.014 --> 37:48.309
There was a video camera
on a tripod to record the pre...

37:50.019 --> 37:53.230
What if he thought the camera...
What if he thought the interview might get...

37:53.356 --> 37:56.150
You know, and he doesn't
want to call a general a liar?

37:56.233 --> 37:57.610
- That's nuts.
- It's not.

37:57.693 --> 38:00.571
He came to us.
He didn't want Sweeney to stand alone.

38:00.696 --> 38:03.658
And if Sweeney's wrong, then I gave
the wrong information to Valenzuela.

38:03.741 --> 38:07.620
Valenzuela's whole interview was goosed
by the information that came before it.

38:07.954 --> 38:10.164
Sweeney says everyone
was wearing MOPP suits.

38:11.123 --> 38:12.291
He told you that?

38:12.375 --> 38:15.378
What if Sweeney's got problems
and what if Valenzuela's his only friend?

38:15.503 --> 38:17.421
Look at line 303.

38:19.840 --> 38:21.592
I don't want Sweeney to stand alone.

38:21.676 --> 38:24.345
He doesn't raise
one original fact in this interview.

38:24.428 --> 38:25.638
Read it again.

38:25.721 --> 38:30.184
By the end, it's a recitation of everything
he's heard from Sweeney and from me.

38:32.728 --> 38:34.772
You need to sleep.

38:40.820 --> 38:41.821
(DOOR OPENS)

38:45.324 --> 38:46.367
A garage?

38:47.076 --> 38:49.412
- Seriously?
- SHEP: They still work.

38:49.495 --> 38:51.497
This place can't afford security monitors.

38:53.207 --> 38:54.709
What brings you to Washington, D.C.?

38:55.084 --> 38:57.586
- We're having trouble with the story.
- No shit.

38:57.670 --> 38:59.839
Tell me one more time we got it right.

38:59.922 --> 39:02.133
You want to see some pictures of David?

39:02.216 --> 39:04.510
- I'm sorry?
- Do you want to see some pictures of David?

39:04.593 --> 39:06.595
- Who's David?
- David's my son, Charlie.

39:06.971 --> 39:08.431
Is there a problem with the story?

39:08.514 --> 39:11.350
There he is.
We're moving him into his dorm at BU.

39:12.393 --> 39:14.311
And here he's home for Thanksgiving.

39:14.437 --> 39:17.189
- Shep.
- Hang on.

39:17.606 --> 39:20.568
That's on the Cape.
We rent a house in August.

39:20.901 --> 39:24.321
Here's a picture
he sent me his first day interning at ACN.

39:25.114 --> 39:29.285
And there he is, first day home
from rehab at Sierra Tucson.

39:29.368 --> 39:32.955
And this one's from his funeral last year.

39:36.876 --> 39:38.377
Jesus, Shep.

39:38.461 --> 39:40.379
I know, I took a picture at a funeral.

39:40.463 --> 39:41.964
That's crazy, but it's just for you.

39:42.882 --> 39:44.300
They call it heron now.

39:44.925 --> 39:46.635
Like the bird, just a little heron.

39:46.802 --> 39:48.137
I didn't have any idea.

39:48.220 --> 39:52.141
You hired him as a summer intern
on his 90th day.

39:52.224 --> 39:54.060
Three months is a landmark in that world.

39:54.143 --> 39:56.729
Three everything... Three days, three weeks,
three months, three years.

39:56.812 --> 39:58.314
Who the fuck knows why?

39:58.731 --> 40:01.817
- Are you sure you don't want to sit?
- We're in a garage!

40:02.818 --> 40:03.986
We can go somewhere.

40:04.070 --> 40:06.072
One of your people, Charlie,
one of your people...

40:06.155 --> 40:08.908
One of your people fired him
and you didn't stop it.

40:08.991 --> 40:11.619
I wish, man... I wish you'd talked.
There's an explanation.

40:11.702 --> 40:13.454
You didn't stop it.

40:13.537 --> 40:16.582
He was a good kid.
He was a smart kid and a worker.

40:16.665 --> 40:19.418
He was a 19-year-old junkie,
but he was clean 90 days.

40:19.502 --> 40:21.587
- Our social media guy runs the interns.
- Neal Sampat.

40:21.670 --> 40:23.339
- David...
- Whose name you didn't know.

40:23.464 --> 40:26.092
...was posting...
Is this something you really want to hear?

40:26.217 --> 40:28.594
Yes. From you, badly.

40:28.677 --> 40:31.722
- I never knew anything...
- He posted something on the Internet?

40:32.181 --> 40:33.808
- Look.
- Yeah?

40:33.891 --> 40:38.229
A couple of years ago,
<i>News Night</i> got a new EP and the show...

40:39.021 --> 40:40.856
Boy, is your wife...

40:40.940 --> 40:42.233
Linda is my ex-wife.

40:42.983 --> 40:44.860
The show took a turn and what?

40:46.862 --> 40:50.324
David posted things about it
on the Internet he didn't like.

40:50.407 --> 40:52.284
Things about...

40:52.368 --> 40:54.370
- He was politically engaged.
- Mmm-hmm.

40:54.453 --> 40:55.788
- Neal...
- Neal Sampat.

40:55.871 --> 41:00.167
Neal warned him he can't do that
and he kept on doing it.

41:00.501 --> 41:02.461
- I'm sorry.
- You didn't step in.

41:03.212 --> 41:04.296
He deserved to be fired.

41:06.966 --> 41:09.218
How many stories have I given you?

41:10.719 --> 41:15.516
There was a moment a while back
I thought about having you killed.

41:16.058 --> 41:18.727
Then I thought, "What does Charlie Skinner
fear more than death?"

41:19.812 --> 41:22.523
"Sit back, wait for your moment."

41:23.732 --> 41:26.861
Then Jerry Dantana starts
calling MARSOCs about Genoa.

41:28.362 --> 41:30.072
The helo manifest you gave me.

41:30.322 --> 41:32.241
Hold it over light for 20 seconds.

41:36.954 --> 41:38.622
CHARLIE: So that happened.

41:39.957 --> 41:41.959
- Are you kidding me?
- No.

41:42.042 --> 41:43.627
Are you kidding me with this story?

41:43.752 --> 41:44.962
No, this is all...

41:45.838 --> 41:48.257
All terribly true.

41:48.340 --> 41:50.801
- (COMPUTER BEEPING)
- There are protests erupting in Cairo.

41:51.594 --> 41:53.679
WILL: <i>March 2, 1955.</i>

41:54.221 --> 41:55.806
A young black woman is arrested

41:55.931 --> 41:59.268
for refusing to give up her seat
on a bus to a white man in Alabama.

41:59.894 --> 42:03.147
Civil rights leaders
and the ACLU rush to her side

42:03.230 --> 42:06.442
and she will be a symbol of the struggle
against segregation.

42:06.525 --> 42:10.321
Her name is Claudette Colvin
and she's 15 years old.

42:10.404 --> 42:11.947
She's also unmarried and pregnant.

42:12.448 --> 42:15.367
Civil rights leaders and the ACLU
decide that Colvin

42:15.451 --> 42:18.662
is not the best foot forward and stand down.

42:18.746 --> 42:20.956
Eight months later, Rosa Parks happens,

42:21.040 --> 42:24.460
but during that eight months,
a brilliant and charismatic young minister

42:24.793 --> 42:29.048
gets the attention of the community
and is chosen to lead the bus boycotts.

42:29.465 --> 42:31.508
If Claudette Colvin doesn't get pregnant,

42:31.592 --> 42:34.511
if they'd gone in the spring
instead of eight months later,

42:34.595 --> 42:38.390
Martin Luther King is a preacher
you've never heard of in Montgomery.

42:38.807 --> 42:40.559
I've got a few hundred people
outside the embassy

42:40.643 --> 42:42.770
- and so far it's peaceful.
- That's what I've got.

42:42.853 --> 42:44.313
- TAMARA: Which embassy?
- Ours.

42:44.396 --> 42:45.397
What are they protesting?

42:45.481 --> 42:46.440
TAMARA: Is anybody getting through
to Cairo?

42:46.523 --> 42:49.235
I've got the front desk at the Shepheard Hotel.
It's a couple blocks away.

42:49.318 --> 42:52.196
He's saying that people have been streaming
toward the embassy for about an hour.

42:52.279 --> 42:54.490
- Is he saying how many?
- He thinks a couple of thousand.

42:54.573 --> 42:56.742
- Thousand?
- A poli sci professor at AU in Cairo

42:56.825 --> 42:59.536
says that a Salafist leader
named Wesam Abdel-Wareth...

42:59.620 --> 43:02.915
He's like the Glenn Beck of Egypt
and he's the president of a television station.

43:03.082 --> 43:05.626
He put out a call to protest a movie
called <i>Muhammad's Tribe.</i>

43:05.709 --> 43:06.752
Why are they at the American embassy?

43:06.835 --> 43:08.796
Apparently it's an American movie,
but we can't find it.

43:09.088 --> 43:10.339
Wait a second.

43:10.464 --> 43:15.010
What's the name of the pastor
with the mustache who's crazy?

43:15.135 --> 43:16.303
- Terry Jones.
- Yes.

43:16.387 --> 43:18.681
He announced yesterday
that he was screening a movie.

43:20.015 --> 43:21.767
- I can't remember the name.
<i>- Innocence of Muslims.</i>

43:22.184 --> 43:23.811
Is it possible it's the same movie?

43:23.894 --> 43:25.437
WILL: Who is Giuseppe Zangara?

43:25.854 --> 43:31.443
I don't really know. He's a guy with a gun
who fired five shots in February 15, 1933,

43:31.527 --> 43:33.570
killing the Mayor of Chicago.

43:33.654 --> 43:36.156
Why? Because Zangara
was standing on a wobbly chair.

43:36.532 --> 43:38.200
And the Mayor of Chicago wasn't his target.

43:38.409 --> 43:39.868
It was the guy the mayor
was shaking hands with,

43:39.952 --> 43:42.788
the newly elected
President Franklin Roosevelt.

43:42.871 --> 43:47.293
If Zangara's chair isn't wobbly,
Roosevelt never takes office

43:47.376 --> 43:50.212
and we swear in his running mate,
John Nance Garner,

43:50.629 --> 43:55.843
a man whose political ideology was the basis
for his opposition to a package of legislation

43:56.135 --> 44:00.472
that would be called The New Deal
and we don't survive the Great Depression.

44:00.556 --> 44:02.182
It's the same movie. <i>Innocence of Muslims.</i>

44:02.266 --> 44:04.268
He changed the title
to get Muslims in to see it.

44:04.351 --> 44:05.644
There's a mash-up of it on YouTube.

44:05.728 --> 44:07.146
Does it seem offensive?

44:07.229 --> 44:08.480
To filmmakers at the very least.

44:08.564 --> 44:12.318
Okay, AP has just reported,
"Egyptian Islamist protestors angry over film

44:12.401 --> 44:14.611
"scale US Embassy wall
in Cairo and tear down flag."

44:14.737 --> 44:15.946
- The American flag.
- I understand that now.

44:16.030 --> 44:17.823
- Jim, this thing's starting to move.
- They breached the wall.

44:17.906 --> 44:18.949
DON: They've got a link to their website

44:19.033 --> 44:20.159
- with a message.
- I'm on their website.

44:20.242 --> 44:22.870
"The Embassy of the United States in Cairo
condemns the continuing efforts

44:22.953 --> 44:25.414
"by misguided individuals
to hurt the religious feelings of Muslims."

44:25.539 --> 44:26.790
They're apologizing for the movie?

44:26.874 --> 44:29.626
2,000 people just hopped the wall, man.
I'd apologize for whatever they want.

44:29.710 --> 44:31.420
- I wouldn't.
- Congratulations.

44:31.503 --> 44:33.756
MargaretJordan@ACN.com.

44:33.839 --> 44:35.591
We'll have video of the flag
in about five minutes.

44:35.674 --> 44:37.134
They took down our flag and replaced it

44:37.217 --> 44:38.927
with a black flag
and in Arabic writing it says...

44:39.053 --> 44:41.430
"There is no God but God
and Muhammad is the prophet of God."

44:41.597 --> 44:43.307
I hope our apology was sincere enough.

44:43.390 --> 44:46.143
You want a job as the guy who answers
the front door of the embassy right now?

44:46.226 --> 44:47.644
We're gonna need more bodies on phones.

44:47.728 --> 44:49.521
Who are we talking to?
Does London know anything?

44:49.605 --> 44:51.523
London? When was the last time you slept?

44:51.607 --> 44:53.942
I've been busy standing by Genoa.
What about you?

44:54.151 --> 44:55.277
I have no problem standing by it.

44:55.652 --> 44:56.904
You were well trained.

44:56.987 --> 44:59.031
Guys, another demonstration's broken out.

44:59.114 --> 45:00.616
- JIM: In Cairo?
- In Libya.

45:00.699 --> 45:02.451
Outside our consulate in Benghazi.

45:02.618 --> 45:04.203
WILL: <i>Your kitchen faucet has washers.</i>

45:04.286 --> 45:06.538
They keep water from leaking
through the joints in the fixtures.

45:06.622 --> 45:07.790
And that's what O-rings do.

45:07.915 --> 45:10.292
They're giant washers
that keep pressurized hydrogen

45:10.417 --> 45:12.961
from leaking out of the SRB,
the solid rocket booster,

45:13.045 --> 45:15.297
that shoots the space shuttle
out of the Earth's atmosphere.

45:16.048 --> 45:17.633
These O-rings have been tested and tested

45:17.716 --> 45:21.261
under every possible
circumstance but one, cold.

45:21.345 --> 45:23.931
They didn't test to see if the O-rings
worked when it was cold.

45:24.014 --> 45:25.391
Why would they even think to test for that?

45:25.474 --> 45:28.477
The thing's launching from south Florida.
When's it gonna be cold?

45:29.103 --> 45:31.146
On January 28, 1986,

45:31.647 --> 45:35.567
a cold snap dragged
the overnight temperature down to 18 degrees

45:35.651 --> 45:39.738
and it turns out the O-rings
stopped working below 40.

45:39.822 --> 45:43.242
So 73 seconds after the <i>Challenger</i> lifts off,

45:43.325 --> 45:46.995
it converts itself into a bomb and detonates.

45:47.079 --> 45:49.373
An American's dead. Don't know who.

45:49.873 --> 45:51.125
- Staff member.
- Consulate staff.

45:51.208 --> 45:53.252
- All this statement says is...
- GARY: Statement from who?

45:53.335 --> 45:55.462
Libya's Supreme Security Committee.

45:55.546 --> 45:58.090
"One American staff member has died
and a number have been injured."

45:58.173 --> 45:59.967
- What's his name?
- We don't know.

46:00.050 --> 46:02.344
I want to stop hearing that answer soon.
We have 90 minutes to air.

46:02.469 --> 46:04.763
- Mac, did you want to look at this?
- Not this second.

46:04.847 --> 46:06.682
- They're not releasing names.
- Names?

46:06.807 --> 46:09.101
- They have more than one?
- I don't know if that was the implication.

46:09.184 --> 46:11.687
- JAKE: Mac.
- It's just an LED readout, right?

46:11.770 --> 46:14.022
Yeah. We put it on brackets on the prompter

46:14.148 --> 46:16.525
and I've got it on remote
from the control room.

46:16.650 --> 46:18.110
A segment is 3 minutes and 50 seconds

46:18.193 --> 46:20.404
and you don't have to be in his ear
at the end of a segment.

46:20.529 --> 46:22.906
He'll appreciate that. Just leave it here.

46:22.990 --> 46:26.076
I'll show it to him and find out what
neurotic superstition he has for not using it.

46:26.160 --> 46:28.537
Copy.

46:28.871 --> 46:32.291
MAN IN VIDEO: <i>Muhammad. Muhammad</i>
<i>the bastard, your lady summons you.</i>

46:32.374 --> 46:34.376
MAN 2: <i>My lady? My lady?</i>

46:35.627 --> 46:37.629
<i>Don't finish it.</i>

46:38.422 --> 46:39.423
(GAGGING)

46:40.424 --> 46:41.842
MAN: <i>I'm watching you.</i>

46:41.925 --> 46:43.844
What would a military response be?

46:44.261 --> 46:47.639
First Marine FAST,
Fleet Antiterrorism Security Team.

46:47.723 --> 46:50.142
They've got... Right, they've got platoons.

46:50.225 --> 46:51.768
- In Spain.
- KENDRA: Rota, Spain.

46:52.227 --> 46:53.896
SLOAN: That's still 12 hours, right?

46:53.979 --> 46:55.647
- GARY: Jim would know.
- Where is he?

46:55.731 --> 46:58.025
GARY: He and Don
are huddled up working on something.

47:15.209 --> 47:17.961
So sometimes it's just the one thing.

47:21.298 --> 47:22.299
(CHIMES)

47:30.766 --> 47:33.310
He lucked out.
He wouldn't have been able to do it

47:33.393 --> 47:35.020
if there had been action in the frame.

47:37.814 --> 47:40.442
JERRY: <i>Were any exceptional</i>
<i>measures used in the operation?</i>

47:40.526 --> 47:42.444
STOMTONOVICH:
<i>Exceptional measures were called for.</i>

47:42.569 --> 47:45.239
- JERRY: <i>Like what?</i>
<i>- We used sarin.</i>

47:45.322 --> 47:48.408
<i>It is right.</i>
<i>It is moral and necessary to use any...</i>

47:49.785 --> 47:51.036
(REWINDS)

47:52.454 --> 47:54.039
<i>We used sarin.</i>

47:54.122 --> 47:55.749
<i>It is right. It is moral...</i>

47:56.250 --> 47:59.294
(REWINDS)

47:59.962 --> 48:02.005
<i>Exceptional measures were called for.</i>

48:02.089 --> 48:03.423
JERRY: <i>Like what?</i>

48:04.841 --> 48:07.928
STOMTONOVICH: <i>We used sarin. It is right.</i>

48:08.011 --> 48:10.389
<i>It is moral and necessary to use any means</i>

48:10.472 --> 48:12.724
<i>in that situation</i>
<i>and the situation they were in.</i>

48:13.016 --> 48:14.810
(BEEPING)

48:16.979 --> 48:17.980
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

48:18.730 --> 48:20.816
You forgot about the shot clock.

48:22.150 --> 48:23.360
Mac.

48:23.902 --> 48:26.321
Hey, easy does it.

48:30.033 --> 48:35.122
The shot clock jumped from 19 to 3 to 2 to 14.

48:48.468 --> 48:49.428
He said it, Mac.

48:49.511 --> 48:50.762
How do you not understand
what you've done?

48:50.846 --> 48:51.888
He said it before we were rolling.

48:51.972 --> 48:53.765
- But I couldn't get him to repeat it.
- We have to retract it.

48:53.849 --> 48:55.601
- He said it to me.
- Do you understand this?

48:55.684 --> 48:57.978
- Did Genoa happen? It happened.
- That we invented evidence

48:58.061 --> 49:00.022
- to support a story of a war crime.
- It happened.

49:00.105 --> 49:02.107
Maggie was there.
She heard him say it. She's just fucked up.

49:02.190 --> 49:03.317
A war crime.

49:03.400 --> 49:04.776
- Yeah, it's a war crime and it happened.
- No one...

49:04.860 --> 49:07.446
We went into Iraq because
he had these things. We don't torture,

49:07.529 --> 49:08.989
- we don't use chemical weapons.
- No one...

49:09.072 --> 49:13.452
I wouldn't have done this on any other story
and I wouldn't have done it unless I was sure!

49:18.874 --> 49:21.335
...is ever going to believe us again.

49:25.005 --> 49:28.383
I think I shouldn't say anything more
until I've talked to a lawyer.

49:32.012 --> 49:34.056
- You're fired.
- I know.

49:40.228 --> 49:42.773
We don't think the protests in Benghazi
has anything to do with the movie.

49:42.856 --> 49:44.858
- We don't think it's a protest.
- What do you think it is?

49:44.941 --> 49:46.693
- A planned, coordinated attack.
- A terrorist attack.

49:46.777 --> 49:48.445
- He's got a source at State.
- We've used him.

49:48.528 --> 49:52.199
He saw an e-mail at the operation center
to White House, Pentagon, and FBI saying

49:52.282 --> 49:55.243
Ansar al-Sharia is claiming credit
for the attack in Benghazi.

49:55.327 --> 49:57.120
Will, the movie might just be a coincidence.

49:57.245 --> 49:59.373
It's not a movie. <i>Avatar</i> is a movie.

49:59.456 --> 50:00.624
How bad is this thing?

50:00.707 --> 50:02.542
- Oh, it's bad.
- It's really not at all good.

50:02.626 --> 50:05.462
You have been nothing but bad news
since you raised your hand at Northwestern.

50:08.256 --> 50:11.009
Don and Jim have a source at State
that says he saw an e-mail.

50:11.093 --> 50:13.428
Ansar al-Sharia is saying they did Benghazi.

50:13.595 --> 50:17.140
May have nothing to do with Cairo
and it's a 9/11 anniversary attack.

50:18.934 --> 50:20.268
What?

50:21.478 --> 50:23.188
Mac?

50:23.271 --> 50:25.607
We have to retract Genoa tonight.

50:28.193 --> 50:30.112
(SUPPRESSES SOB)

50:30.529 --> 50:32.447
All of it.

50:56.555 --> 50:58.849
WILL: <i>A half an hour later,</i>
<i>we retracted the story.</i>

51:00.475 --> 51:02.352
That was our top story, not Benghazi.

51:02.519 --> 51:05.063
On Benghazi we didn't trust
the source at State.

51:05.188 --> 51:06.898
We didn't trust anything anymore.

51:06.982 --> 51:09.276
We reported the same thing as everybody else

51:09.359 --> 51:11.486
even though we knew
we were probably wrong.

51:11.570 --> 51:15.407
<i>Protesters, angry over an amateur American</i>
<i>movie denouncing Islam,</i>

51:15.532 --> 51:18.827
<i>attacked the United States</i>
<i>consulate in Benghazi, Libya, today,</i>

51:18.952 --> 51:20.871
<i>killing a State Department officer.</i>

51:20.996 --> 51:24.541
<i>While in Cairo, demonstrators stormed</i>
<i>the walls of the United States Embassy.</i>

51:25.375 --> 51:27.252
<i>On the anniversary of 9/1 1...</i>

51:35.594 --> 51:37.888
We just stopped being good at...

51:43.518 --> 51:46.313
Genoa was a real mission. It was successful.

51:47.063 --> 51:49.608
Sweeney was right about the MOPP suits,

51:49.691 --> 51:52.194
just wrong about
the reason they were wearing them.

51:52.277 --> 51:55.197
It was in case
the militants had biological weapons.

51:55.322 --> 51:57.824
The white phosphorus
was only laid down to mark the target.

51:57.908 --> 51:59.785
Hamni8 didn't die in the raid.

51:59.868 --> 52:01.870
His prepaid cell plan ran out.

52:03.038 --> 52:05.040
It was an institutional failure.

52:05.290 --> 52:07.626
(SCOFFS) Bullshit.

52:09.503 --> 52:12.798
We'll call the election tomorrow
and then resign.

52:12.881 --> 52:15.050
She's on her way over.
We're meeting her upstairs.

52:16.218 --> 52:19.429
I'm sorry, Will. I really am.

52:19.554 --> 52:21.473
I wanted this to go another way.

52:24.059 --> 52:26.144
We both knew it wasn't gonna.

52:35.195 --> 52:36.404
WILL: <i>Did she seem mad?</i>

52:37.906 --> 52:38.907
CHARLIE: Hmm?

52:39.366 --> 52:41.201
When you talked to her on the phone.

52:41.284 --> 52:43.495
CHARLIE: It's after midnight.
You think we got her out of bed?

52:43.578 --> 52:46.748
You did not get me out of bed. Good night.

52:46.873 --> 52:49.000
I just paid $1,000 to see <i>Skyfall</i>

52:49.084 --> 52:51.503
and attend a party
at the Museum of Modern Art.

52:51.586 --> 52:54.172
The proceeds are going
to the Tribeca Film Festival.

52:54.256 --> 52:55.924
- You know why?
- To support the arts?

52:56.007 --> 52:58.635
- To meet Daniel Craig.
- Did you?

52:58.760 --> 53:00.595
Hurricane Sandy and the airports.

53:00.846 --> 53:03.849
- He wasn't there?
- He was not there.

53:03.932 --> 53:05.934
You look like Daniel Craig. Get up.

53:07.936 --> 53:11.356
Oh, you look less like him now.
Sit back down. And what about you?

53:12.274 --> 53:14.150
Why so glum, sugarplum?

53:14.234 --> 53:18.530
We're gonna resign, Leona.
It's what has to happen now.

53:18.613 --> 53:24.703
Elliot Hirsch, Sloan Sabbith,
Terry Smith, <i>Dayside ACN,</i> ACN.

53:24.786 --> 53:27.455
We understand the integrity of the news
is more important...

53:27.581 --> 53:30.208
Than one individual. That is beautiful.

53:31.209 --> 53:32.794
Not as beautiful as Daniel Craig.

53:32.878 --> 53:34.671
- Leona.
- I'd have sent my plane.

53:34.754 --> 53:37.090
- I'd have sent my plane.
- We're not fucking around.

53:37.173 --> 53:41.136
You will resign when I fire you
out of petty malice and not before.

53:41.219 --> 53:43.054
- Our trust numbers are...
- Yeah, they're bad.

53:43.138 --> 53:44.222
They're fatal.

53:44.306 --> 53:46.308
Firing Jerry was obviously
the right thing to do,

53:46.433 --> 53:49.019
but it wasn't enough
and we've known that for two months.

53:49.102 --> 53:51.104
Charlie and I have to go.

53:51.563 --> 53:53.857
- And Twiggy over here?
- It was my fault.

53:53.940 --> 53:58.069
McMac. Can I call you McMac?
Doesn't matter, I'm gonna anyway, McMac.

53:58.570 --> 54:01.156
- Your head's up your ass.
- Mrs. Lansing.

54:01.281 --> 54:03.783
Guy comes in here into my hizzy...

54:03.867 --> 54:05.994
Guy comes in here,
cooks an interview, no remorse.

54:06.745 --> 54:09.247
30 lawyers vet the story, it goes on air.

